div.div: Rename article ID for clarity on hypomania vs. hypermania distinction
Remove Learning Resources component to streamline article structure

Add comprehensive articles on learning disabilities and the differences between hypomania and hypermania
- Updated "Growing Up with Learning Disabilities" article with additional preface, sections on mental health impacts, educational tools, and support resources. - Introduced new article "The Difference Between Hypomania and Hypermania" detailing characteristics, diagnosis, treatment approaches, and community support for mood disorders.

Enhance article on hypomania vs. hypermania by expanding preface, sections, and conclusion to provide a comprehensive overview of the conditions, their clinical features, treatment strategies, and available resources for support.
Refactor URL formatting functions to handle additional special characters for improved consistency and reliability.
Consolidate introduction text for various mental health resources to improve readability and coherence.

Enhance article on Disinhibited Social Engagement Disorder by expanding preface, sections, and conclusion to provide a comprehensive overview of the disorder, its causes, symptoms, and treatment strategies for affected children.

Enhance article on multi-diagnosed personality disorders by expanding preface, sections, and conclusion to provide deeper insights into the complexities, challenges, and coping strategies for individuals with multiple diagnoses.

Refactor article titles for clarity and consistency, updating "Understanding Narcissistic Personality Disorder: Myths and Facts" to "Understanding The Myths and Facts Around Narcissistic Personality Disorder" and correcting the title of "Identifying-paranoid-personality-disorder" to "Identifying Paranoid Personality Disorder".
Enhance article on ADHD in adults by expanding sections on symptoms, emotional impact, and treatment strategies to improve understanding and support for affected individuals.
Refactor import to use updated disorder categories for improved resource organization

Adds comprehensive categories for various mental health disorders, including mood, anxiety, personality, trauma, psychotic, eating, and neurodevelopmental disorders, to enhance resource organization and accessibility.
Adds article on Narcissistic Personality Disorder, addressing myths, symptoms, causes, and treatment options to enhance understanding and support for affected individuals.

Refactor articles for improved readability by consolidating sentences in prefaces, supporting sections, and conclusions across multiple articles, including those on bipolar disorder, communication and conduct disorders, narcissistic personality disorder, PTSD, schizophrenia, and the intersection of mood and personality disorders. This enhances clarity and flow while maintaining the integrity of the content.
Removes article on mental health in LGBTQ+ youth from constants; updates title format for DSED article
Adds article on the stages of depression with detailed descriptions and treatment options

Adds slug generation function for URL-friendly titles
Implements a new function to create slugs from titles, ensuring they are URL-friendly by removing unwanted characters and normalizing spaces and hyphens.
This enhances the utility of the format module for generating consistent and clean URLs from given titles.
Adds optional list property to ListDetail type for nested lists
Removes mental health article on LGBTQ+ youth from constants
Refactors article layout and data handling; removes unused imports and simplifies component structure

Adds event filtering and display functionality
Implements filtering options for event types, allowing users to filter events displayed based on their type.
Adds a button interface for selecting different event types and updates the event rendering logic to reflect the selected filter.
Enhances user experience by making it easier to browse through hosted events.
Removes outdated article on grief and loss and adds new articles on bipolar disorder, anxiety disorders, and trauma responses for enhanced mental health resources
Refactors BlogarticleData component to simplify title rendering and improve readability
Removes unnecessary wrapper elements from Layout component for cleaner structure
Refactors Blog component layout for improved readability and updates heading to emphasize mental health focus
Renames toolModule to articleModule for clarity in getArticleData function

Adds detailed resources for various mental health disorders including Social Anxiety Disorder, Specific Phobias, Autism Spectrum Disorder, Dissociative Identity Disorder, and Premenstrual Dysphoric Disorder.

Refactors Blog component to use useSearchParams hook
Improves the Blog component by replacing the manual search parameter handling with the useSearchParams hook for better readability and efficiency.
Ensures proper parsing of the page number and category from the URL, maintaining the notFound functionality for invalid page numbers.
This change streamlines state management and enhances code clarity.

Adds articles on mental health topics including eating disorders, grief, LGBTQ+ youth, substance abuse, schizophrenia, panic disorder, anxiety, PTSD, OCD, BPD, and ADHD for comprehensive resource coverage.
Adds HelplineEntry interface for structured helpline information representation
Renames ArticleCategory interface to Category for consistency and updates references in ArticleIntro
Refactors Blog component to unwrap searchParams for improved readability and consistency
Fix import order for Footer component in layout.tsx
Adds HelplineList component to display crisis helpline information
Adds Resource interfaces for structured resource management and content representation
Refactors Categories component to use MenubarMenu for improved category selection and UI consistency
Adds crisis helpline directory for enhanced support resources
Adds HelplineList component to the Helplines page for improved support visibility
Adds comprehensive learning resources for various mental health disorders
Refactors article categories to enhance clarity and detail, updates data structure and adds comprehensive overviews for mental health categories

Enforces subtitle as a required field in ArticleCategory
Updates the ArticleCategory interface to make the subtitle property mandatory.
This change improves data consistency by ensuring that all articles have a subtitle defined, which can enhance user experience and content clarity.

Updates navigation menu for improved user engagement
Renames and restructures menu items to better reflect the organization's focus on community involvement and resources.
Adds new links for "About Us," "Get Involved," and "Programs & Services" to enhance user access to important information.
Replaces outdated labels with more relevant options, promoting a user-friendly experience and clearer navigation.

Improves ThemeToggle component styling and functionality
Updates the ThemeToggle component to enhance its appearance and behavior.
Changes include adjusting the `className` for a more transparent background and modifying the `pressed` state to reflect the light theme instead of dark.
Additionally, introduces a `data-state` attribute to indicate the current theme state, improving accessibility and user experience.

Adds new service categories and session details for mental health support
Introduces multiple new service categories, including peer support groups, workshops, and counseling sessions, aimed at enhancing mental health resources.
Each category features detailed descriptions, benefits, hosting information, and fees to provide clear guidance and improve accessibility for users seeking support.
These additions aim to create a comprehensive directory of mental health services for community engagement and awareness.

Adds fundraising and volunteer pages
Introduces two new components for fundraising and volunteer opportunities.
These pages provide information and links to respective forms, enhancing user engagement and support for the organization's mission.

Updates About Us page content to reflect new mission
Replaces existing text with a detailed description of InnerLight Elevation's mission, vision, and values.
The update emphasizes a commitment to mental wellness, inclusivity, and community support, aligning the content with the organization's goals.
This change enhances the clarity and relevance of the information presented to visitors.

Enhances diversity and inclusion content on pages
Adds comprehensive diversity and inclusion statements to the Diversity and Inclusion page, emphasizing the organization's commitment to accessible mental health care for all backgrounds.
Updates the Mental Health Pledge with detailed commitments to empathy, understanding, and advocacy for mental wellness.
Revises the Donors page to express gratitude and highlight the impact of donor contributions on expanding mental health initiatives and community outreach.

Adds about section with goals, values, staff, and stats
Introduces a comprehensive about section detailing the organization's goals, core values, staff directory, key statistics, donor recognition, impact stories, and a timeline of milestones.
This enhancement aims to clearly communicate the mission and impact of the organization, fostering transparency and connection with stakeholders.
Relates to documentation and user engagement improvements.
feat: add Helplines component to provide support resources
feat: enhance MenuBarNav with router integration for improved navigation
feat: implement HoverEffect component for enhanced UI interaction on category display
feat: update homepage content to enhance mental health awareness messaging

feat: add new UI components including Input, Separator, Sheet, Sidebar, Skeleton, Sonner, Switch, ToggleGroup, and Tooltip
- Introduced Input component for text input fields. - Added Separator component for visual separation of UI elements. - Implemented Sheet component for modal-like overlays. - Created Sidebar component for navigation with collapsible functionality. - Developed Skeleton component for loading placeholders. - Integrated Sonner component for notifications using the Toaster library. - Built Switch component for toggle functionality. - Established ToggleGroup and ToggleGroupItem components for grouped toggle buttons. - Added Tooltip component for displaying additional information on hover.
Fix formatting in globals.css and enhance base styles for consistent theming
Update dependencies in package.json and package-lock.json

Add new pages for Diversity and Inclusion Statement, Mental Health Pledge, Our Partners, Our Staff, About Us, Learning Resources, Donors, Donations, Events, Event Stories Overview, Helplines, Programs and Services, and Testimonials
Add ServiceCategory and ServiceMeeting interfaces for service management

Refactor articles related to mood disorders and depression
- Updated the article section for cognitive behavioral therapy exercises to focus on mood disorders, specifically depression. - Created a new article titled "The Stages of Depression" with detailed sections on mild, moderate, and severe depression, including symptoms, seeking help, and self-care strategies. - Removed several articles that were previously included in the articles list to streamline content. - Modified the ArticleCategory and ArticleIntro interfaces to better reflect the structure of articles, including changes to the properties for clarity and consistency. - Added references to the new article for further reading and support resources.
Removes awareness articles from the constants module
Adds date formatting and URL ID conversion utilities

Adds article-related interfaces for structured content
Introduces TypeScript interfaces for managing article categories, introductions, and content structures.
These additions enable better organization and type safety for article-related data throughout the application.

Adds comprehensive mental health resource tools
Introduces a collection of articles and guides focused on various mental health practices, including cognitive-behavioral therapy exercises, mindfulness techniques, and resilience-building tools.
These resources aim to empower individuals by providing structured approaches to improve emotional well-being, enhance coping mechanisms, and foster self-reflection.
The additions support a holistic approach to mental health and aim to create lasting positive changes in users' lives.

Adds social media icons and article context provider
Introduces new SVG components for social media icons, enhancing the UI with visual elements for X, Instagram, GitHub, and LinkedIn.
Implements an ArticleContext provider to manage and share article data across components, improving state management and accessibility in the application.
Updates the MenuBarNav styling for better alignment and spacing in the layout.

Adds Container components for layout management
Introduces `ContainerOuter`, `ContainerInner`, and a wrapper `Container` component to enhance layout capabilities in the application.
These components utilize `forwardRef` for better reference handling and leverage `clsx` for dynamic class management, providing a more flexible and responsive design structure.

Adds blog article data component for dynamic content rendering
Introduces a new component to fetch and display blog article data based on the URL slug.
Implements dynamic loading of article content, including titles, subtitles, images, sections, and conclusions, enhancing the user experience by providing tailored content.
This change improves maintainability by allowing articles to be easily added or updated through modular imports.

Adds layout component for article detail pages
Implements a new layout component that provides context for article detail pages.
It integrates the ArticleProvider to manage article-related state and displays the article title and description dynamically based on the URL path.
This enhances the user experience by ensuring relevant information is presented for each article.

Adds article listing and category filtering component
Implements a new page for displaying articles with category filtering and pagination functionality.
Includes reusable components for categories and posts, enhancing user navigation and content discovery.
This update improves the user experience by organizing articles and allowing easier access to specific content based on categories.
